2.service, food took about an hour to arrive, although considering there was like 2 other people there it probably shouldnt have taken this long, waiter was superrrr slow and came by the table to remove our plates after we finished eating for like 4 times when it only needed once, once again the service isnt that bad but definitely not good,they did give us a free icecream at the end as a thank u, 2.5/5

3.food, we ordered the mushroom and chicken white sauce pasta, the pepperoni pizza and the crispy chicken sandwich, pasta was good but nothing too special i've had better, pizza wasnt crispy at all, it was too gooey and the crust was undercooked, pepperoni was sliced which doesnt make a big difference in the taste but it definitely looks better unsliced, the sandwich was dry and didnt have any sauces, chicken wasnt warm and was hard to bite, very dry and hard to chew, wasnt good, overall as someone who doesnt go outside much i was disapointed, definitely could have enjoyed my evening more if i ate somewhere else, however prices were good but i could have payed the same amount somewhere else and got better food, overall experience is 3/5
